value.0: Falcons are majestic birds, often trained by adventurers to be loyal companions. Their superior eyesight and speed are their greatest assets.
No visitors, well wishers or do-gooders, PLEASE!!

The plant where the ever-popular sweetberries grow. Fairly small-sized, these plants have been actually known to grow to larger sizes as house plants, although this practice is rather uncommon. Perhaps due to the fey that usually bother the houses which have the plants potted...

The Sweetberry is a highly prized item for Cordorian children, to others, completely useless.  Commonly stuck on the end of a stick and licked, the sweetberry has a powerfully sweet taste that most adults find overwhelming.  Except in Amia, where they are enjoyed by almost all, sometimes even a little too much, in the case of an ex-assassin who craves them with a passion.
No visitors, well wishers or do-gooders, PLEASE!!

This birch tree has been abused in its unfortunate location. Scratches and chips run along the first three feet of its trunk above the ground, while above the leaves are untouched and heavy in the branches.

Three massive claw marks mar the surface of the trunk much higher than the smaller scrapes below it.

This tree appears to be much darker than the other trees in the vicinity. It is mangled and devoid of leaves, and yet it seems to be very much alive. At its base is a small hollow filled with old burlap sacks that have long been picked clean of their contents.
This boulder appears to have been charred black. The earth surrounding it is untouched.
This blood appears to be relatively fresh. Whatever caused it could still be nearby and was intelligent enough not to track the blood beyond the statue's location.
